<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1436,470,890]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<taxonomicName box="[151,329,470,494]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Phalonidia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tolli">
<emphasis box="[151,329,470,494]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Phalonidia tolli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described from the male 
<typeStatus box="[673,771,470,494]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">holotype</typeStatus>
(
<figureCitation box="[787,875,470,494]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 A – 8 C" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1636,1659]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,176,1597]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[151,1436,175,1653]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 8 A – 8 C. Holotype of Phalonidia tolli Razowski, 1960. Fig. 8 A: adult male. Fig. 8 B: male genitalia (phallus removed). Fig. 8 C: Phallus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/208394/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Fig. 
<number box="[841,853,470,494]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="8.0">8</number>
A
</figureCitation>
–C) collected 
<date box="[1035,1187,470,494]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="1938-06-25">
<number box="[1035,1063,470,494]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="25.0">25</number>
June 
<quantity box="[1131,1187,470,494]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.92252" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" unit="in" value="1938.0">1938</quantity>
</date>
in 
<collectingCountry box="[1225,1295,470,494]" name="China" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">China</collectingCountry>
, Manchuria, prov. Kirin, Djalantun (
<bibRefCitation author="Razowski" box="[434,621,506,530]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" refString="Razowski, J. (1960) Studies on the Cochylidae (Lepidoptera). Part III. On some species from the collection of Dr. S. Toll. Polskie Pismo entomologiczne, 30, 397 - 402." type="journal article" year="1960">
Razowski 
<number box="[561,621,506,530]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="1960.0">1960</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). Razowski later (
<number box="[844,903,506,530]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="1970.0">1970</number>
) synonymised this taxon with 
<taxonomicName box="[1282,1428,508,531]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Phalonidia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="manniana">
<emphasis box="[1282,1428,508,531]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">P. manniana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, although with doubts, as an examination of European material revealed that the male genitalia of 
<taxonomicName box="[1293,1436,543,567]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Phalonidia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="manniana">
<emphasis box="[1293,1436,543,567]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">P. manniana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
exhibit some variation. He concluded that the problem of intrapecific variation could only be resolved with additional material from Manchuria (
<bibRefCitation author="Razowski" box="[574,756,614,638]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" refString="Razowski, J. (1970) Cochylidae. In: Amsel, H. G., Gregor, F., Reisser, H., (Eds.), Microlepidoptera Palaearctica, 3, Vienna, pp. 1 - 528, 161 pls." type="journal article" year="1970">
Razowski 
<number box="[696,756,614,638]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="1970.0">1970</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). We examined the 
<typeStatus box="[984,1082,614,638]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">holotype</typeStatus>
and it agrees with 
<taxonomicName box="[1305,1405,614,639]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Cochylis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="udana">
<emphasis box="[1305,1405,614,639]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">P. udana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in characters of the male genitalia, particularly the shape of the valva with the acute angle between the sacculus and the cucullus. The median process of the transtilla is relatively short, but falls within the range of variation we have seen in our material of 
<taxonomicName box="[416,514,723,747]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Cochylis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="udana">
<emphasis box="[416,514,723,747]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">P. udana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[531,611,722,746]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1924,1947]" captionTargetBox="[151,1411,210,1845]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,193,1903]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 7. Comparison of valvae of Phalonidia manniana and P. udana with C. notulana lectotype, C. udana lectotype and P. tolli holotype included." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/208393/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Figs. 
<number box="[595,611,723,746]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="7.8">7</number>
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[624,638,722,746]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 A – 8 C" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1636,1659]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,176,1597]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[151,1436,175,1653]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 8 A – 8 C. Holotype of Phalonidia tolli Razowski, 1960. Fig. 8 A: adult male. Fig. 8 B: male genitalia (phallus removed). Fig. 8 C: Phallus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/208394/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">8</figureCitation>
B, 
<number box="[672,685,722,746]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="8.0">8</number>
C). The wings are rather rubbed, but the dorsal half of the median fascia is heavily suffused with dark scales (
<figureCitation box="[632,718,758,782]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 A – 8 C" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1636,1659]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,176,1597]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[151,1436,175,1653]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 8 A – 8 C. Holotype of Phalonidia tolli Razowski, 1960. Fig. 8 A: adult male. Fig. 8 B: male genitalia (phallus removed). Fig. 8 C: Phallus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/208394/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Fig. 
<number box="[684,697,758,782]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="8.0">8</number>
A
</figureCitation>
). This is not indicative of either 
<taxonomicName box="[1082,1220,759,783]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Phalonidia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="manniana">
<emphasis box="[1082,1220,759,783]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">P. manniana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName box="[1257,1354,758,783]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Cochylis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="udana">
<emphasis box="[1257,1354,758,783]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">P. udana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Based on the male genitalia we conclude that 
<taxonomicName box="[598,672,795,819]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Phalonidia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tolli">
<emphasis box="[598,672,795,819]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">P. tolli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName box="[946,1045,795,819]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Cochylis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="udana" status="syn. nov.">
<emphasis box="[946,1045,795,819]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">P. udana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1060,1165,795,819]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1060,1165,795,819]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">syn. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
It is, however, possible that 
<taxonomicName box="[201,275,830,855]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Phalonidia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tolli">
<emphasis box="[201,275,830,855]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">P. tolli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
represents a third species and the revised synonymy with 
<taxonomicName box="[938,1037,830,855]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Cochylis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="udana">
<emphasis box="[938,1037,830,855]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">P. udana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
remains to be verified with further material from the Far East.
</paragraph>
